ver formerly operated a fishing camp on Florida's east coast. When the De Land pool formed, Oliver volunteered and turned out to be a first class machinist who had learned his trade in Oklahoma. Now he is assembly machinist in the plant, able to handle any job that comes along. He is typical of the retired skilled machinists being discovered daily in the state by pool operators]", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017868576/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2017868577/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017868577/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2017868577/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/fsa/item/2017868577/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/fsa/item/2017868577/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/fsa.8d37079/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2017868577", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/fsa.8d37079"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["hollem, howard r."], "date": "1942-01-01", "dates": ["1942"], "description": ["1 negative : nitrate ; 4 x 5 inches or smaller."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-09-01T20:28:37.074Z", "group": ["fsa", "catalog-split-03", "catalog", "fsa-owi-black-and-white-negatives", "main-catalog-split-03", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017868577/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8d37000/8d37000/8d37079_150px.jpg#h=113&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8d37000/8d37000/8d37079t.gif#h=113&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8d37000/8d37000/8d37079r.jpg#h=481&w=640", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8d37000/8d37000/8d37079v.jpg#h=769&w=1024"], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["volusia county", "united states", "de land", "florida"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/owi2001042309/pp", "2021-04-06t10:40:15", "2017868577", "http://www.loc.gov/item/20072716", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017868577"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["farm security administration/office of war information black-and-white negatives", "prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "prints and photographs division", "american memory", "catalog"], "score": 35.843044, "shelf_id": "LC-USW3- 056258-C [P&P]", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["de land", "nitrate negatives", "volusia county", "united states", "florida"], "timestamp": "2022-04-26T10:48:57.193Z", "title": "[Untitled photo, possibly related to: De Land pool. Babcock airplane plant. Earl Gentry was a beverage salesman faced with the loss of his job by the impact of war. He completed 250 hours of training in the De Land, Florida vocational school. Now he's a first-class welder in the Babcock plant in De Land]", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017868577/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2017868578/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017868578/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2017868578/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/fsa/item/2017868578/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/fsa/item/2017868578/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/fsa.8d43339/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/fsa.8d43339", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2017868578"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["palmer, alfred t."], "date": "1942-01-01", "dates": ["1942"], "description": ["1 negative : safety ; 4 x 5 inches or smaller."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-09-01T20:26:50.800Z", "group": ["fsa", "catalog-split-04", "catalog", "fsa-owi-black-and-white-negatives", "main-catalog-split-04", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017868578/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8d43000/8d43300/8d43339_150px.jpg#h=119&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8d43000/8d43300/8d43339t.gif#h=119&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-